On the relationships between the theory, methodology and empirical studies in social sciences. Research paradigms. Quantitative and qualitative approaches, their combination and triangulation. The system of methods. Research strategies. Primary and secondary data. Social measurement. Conceptualisation. Indicators. Reliability and validity. General population and sample. Types of sampling. Research ethics in social sciences. Stages of research. Research project.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The objective of the course is to give thorough knowledge of the general methodology of social sciences and provide basic knowledge for further independent work with methodological literature.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After passing the course a student: * knows the main terms and conceptions of the methodology of social sciences; * is able to reflect critically upon his/her methodological experiences; * is able to write a social scientific research project
